tafsir[3]{c,v,t}:
  33,63,"The people will question thee concerning the Hour. Say: 'The knowledge of it is only with God; what shall make thee know? Haply the Hour is nigh.'"
  33,65,"therein to dwell for ever; they shall find neither protector nor helper."
  33,71,"and He will set right your deeds for you and will forgive you your sins. Whosoever obeys God and His Messenger has won a mighty triumph."